<h2 id="one-sided-limits">One-sided limits</h2>
<p><img src="/assets/img/5.jpg" alt="" class="mr" /></p>

<p>$lim_{x \to 2} f(x) = $ ?</p>

<p>Right-sided: $lim_{x \to a^+} f(x)$</p>

<p>$lim_{x \to 2^+} f(x)=1$</p>

<p>Left-sided: $lim_{x \to a^-} f(x)$</p>

<p>$lim_{x \to 2^-} f(x)=-1$</p>

<p>Note: For a limit to exist at ‚Äòa‚Äô $lim_{x \to a} f(x)=L$ you must have:
\[lim_{x \to a^-} f(x)=lim_{x \to a^+} f(x)\]</p>

<p class="clearfix"></p>

<p>EXAMPLE<br />
Find limit of $f(x)=\frac{1}{x}$ as $x \rightarrow 0$</p>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th style="text-align: center">x</th>
      <th style="text-align: center">-0.5</th>
      <th style="text-align: center">-0.1</th>
      <th style="text-align: center">-0.001</th>
      <th style="text-align: center">0</th>
      <th style="text-align: center">0.001</th>
      <th style="text-align: center">0.01</th>
      <th style="text-align: center">0.5</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td style="text-align: center">f(x)</td>
      <td style="text-align: center">-2</td>
      <td style="text-align: center">-100</td>
      <td style="text-align: center">-1000</td>
      <td style="text-align: center">/</td>
      <td style="text-align: center">1000</td>
      <td style="text-align: center">100</td>
      <td style="text-align: center">2</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p>\[lim_{x \to 0^-} \frac{1}{x} = -\infty \quad\quad\quad 
lim_{x \to 0^+} \frac{1}{x} = +\infty\]</p>

<p>* If $lim_{x \to a^\pm} f(x) = \pm\infty$</p>
